snippet.title: Meeting of the Maryland State Board of Education - Tuesday April 25th, 2023
snippet.description:
To continue dialogue with our stakeholders, we have developed an online form for anyone interested in engaging with MSDE. Please share this with your networks, so we can gain a deeper understanding of diverse family education experiences across the state. To access this MSDE Engagement Form, please click the following link: https://bit.ly/3K2hdEf

AGENDA ITEMS 
08:41  Meeting Opening
13:04  Public Comment
32:20  New Business
33:16  Stakeholder Engagement Session – Milken Educator Awards Recognition
59:11  Legislative Update 
1:32:14  Priorities – School Profile: Salem Avenue Elementary School (Washington County Public Schools)
3:40:39  Priorities – Blueprint Deep Dive: College and Career Readiness Exploratory Study Findings 
4:13:30  Priorities – Reducing Overidentification and Narrowing Achievement Gaps Case Study: Lexington Public Schools (Lexington, MA)
5:34:00  Reports to State Board for Discussion/Action
5:44:05  Adjourn to Executive Session
8:00:37  State Board Member Committee Reports/Updates
8:05:15  Future Board Agenda Topics
8:05:39  Opinions
8:07:28  Adjourn
